  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: f0e13320f8bc1254f8bca32b62d9305b, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Greeting to the Twelve TribesProfiting from Trials'
      title: Greeting to the Twelve TribesProfiting from Trials
      number: 1
      content: James, a bondservant of God and of the Lord Jesus Christ,To the twelve
        tribes which are scattered abroad:Greetings.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'My brethren, count it all joy when you fall into various trials, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'knowing that the testing of your faith produces patience. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But let patience have its perfect work, that you may be perfect and
        complete, lacking nothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'If any of you lacks wisdom, let him ask of God, who gives to all
        liberally and without reproach, and it will be given to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But let him ask in faith, with no doubting, for he who doubts is
        like a wave of the sea driven and tossed by the wind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For let not that man suppose that he will receive anything from the
        Lord; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Perspective of Rich and Poor'
      title: The Perspective of Rich and Poor
      number: 8
      content: he  is  a double-minded man, unstable in all his ways.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Let the lowly brother glory in his exaltation, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'but the rich in his humiliation, because as a flower of the field
        he will pass away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Loving God Under Trials'
      title: Loving God Under Trials
      number: 11
      content: For no sooner has the sun risen with a burning heat than it withers
        the grass; its flower falls, and its beautiful appearance perishes. So the
        rich man also will fade away in his pursuits.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Blessed is the man who endures temptation; for when he has been approved,
        he will receive the crown of life which the Lord has promised to those who
        love Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Let no one say when he is tempted, \u201CI am tempted by God\u201D;
        for God cannot be tempted by evil, nor does He Himself tempt anyone. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But each one is tempted when he is drawn away by his own desires
        and enticed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Then, when desire has conceived, it gives birth to sin; and sin, when
        it is full-grown, brings forth death.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Do not be deceived, my beloved brethren. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Every good gift and every perfect gift is from above, and comes down
        from the Father of lights, with whom there is no variation or shadow of turning. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Qualities Needed in Trials'
      title: Qualities Needed in Trials
      number: 18
      content: Of His own will He brought us forth by the word of truth, that we
        might be a kind of firstfruits of His creatures.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So then, my beloved brethren, let every man be swift to hear, slow
        to speak, slow to wrath; '
      comments: []
    - name: "20: Doers\u2014Not Hearers Only"
      title: "Doers\u2014Not Hearers Only"
      number: 20
      content: for the wrath of man does not produce the righteousness of God.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Therefore lay aside all filthiness and overflow of wickedness, and
        receive with meekness the implanted word, which is able to save your souls.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But be doers of the word, and not hearers only, deceiving yourselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For if anyone is a hearer of the word and not a doer, he is like
        a man observing his natural face in a mirror; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'for he observes himself, goes away, and immediately forgets what
        kind of man he was. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: But he who looks into the perfect law of liberty and continues in 
        it, and is not a forgetful hearer but a doer of the work, this one will be
        blessed in what he does.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "If anyone among you thinks he is religious, and does not bridle his
        tongue but deceives his own heart, this one\u2019s religion is useless. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Pure and undefiled religion before God and the Father is this: to
        visit orphans and widows in their trouble, and to keep oneself unspotted
        from the world.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Beware of Personal Favoritism'
      title: Beware of Personal Favoritism
      number: 1
      content: 'My brethren, do not hold the faith of our Lord Jesus Christ, the 
        Lord of glory, with partiality. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For if there should come into your assembly a man with gold rings,
        in fine apparel, and there should also come in a poor man in filthy clothes, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and you pay attention to the one wearing the fine clothes and say
        to him, \u201CYou sit here in a good place,\u201D and say to the poor man,
        \u201CYou stand there,\u201D or, \u201CSit here at my footstool,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: have you not shown partiality among yourselves, and become judges
        with evil thoughts?
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Listen, my beloved brethren: Has God not chosen the poor of this
        world to  be  rich in faith and heirs of the kingdom which He promised to
        those who love Him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But you have dishonored the poor man. Do not the rich oppress you
        and drag you into the courts? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Do they not blaspheme that noble name by which you are called?
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "If you really fulfill the royal law according to the Scripture, \u201CYou
        shall love your neighbor as yourself,\u201D you do well; "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'but if you show partiality, you commit sin, and are convicted by
        the law as transgressors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For whoever shall keep the whole law, and yet stumble in one point, 
        he is guilty of all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For He who said, \u201CDo not commit adultery,\u201D also said, \u201CDo
        not murder.\u201D Now if you do not commit adultery, but you do murder, you
        have become a transgressor of the law. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So speak and so do as those who will be judged by the law of liberty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Faith Without Works Is Dead'
      title: Faith Without Works Is Dead
      number: 13
      content: For judgment is without mercy to the one who has shown no mercy. Mercy
        triumphs over judgment.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'What does  it profit, my brethren, if someone says he has faith but
        does not have works? Can faith save him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'If a brother or sister is naked and destitute of daily food, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "and one of you says to them, \u201CDepart in peace, be warmed and
        filled,\u201D but you do not give them the things which are needed for the
        body, what does  it profit? "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Thus also faith by itself, if it does not have works, is dead.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But someone will say, \u201CYou have faith, and I have works.\u201D
        Show me your faith without your works, and I will show you my faith by my
        works. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "You believe that there is one God. You do well. Even the demons believe\u2014and
        tremble! "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But do you want to know, O foolish man, that faith without works
        is dead? '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Was not Abraham our father justified by works when he offered Isaac
        his son on the altar? '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Do you see that faith was working together with his works, and by
        works faith was made perfect? '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And the Scripture was fulfilled which says, \u201CAbraham believed
        God, and it was accounted to him for righteousness.\u201D And he was called
        the friend of God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: You see then that a man is justified by works, and not by faith only.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Likewise, was not Rahab the harlot also justified by works when she
        received the messengers and sent them out another way?
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: For as the body without the spirit is dead, so faith without works
        is dead also.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Untamable Tongue'
      title: The Untamable Tongue
      number: 1
      content: 'My brethren, let not many of you become teachers, knowing that we
        shall receive a stricter judgment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For we all stumble in many things. If anyone does not stumble in
        word, he is a perfect man, able also to bridle the whole body. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Indeed, we put bits in horses\u2019 mouths that they may obey us,
        and we turn their whole body. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Look also at ships: although they are so large and are driven by
        fierce winds, they are turned by a very small rudder wherever the pilot desires. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Even so the tongue is a little member and boasts great things.See
        how great a forest a little fire kindles! '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the tongue is a fire, a world of iniquity. The tongue is so set
        among our members that it defiles the whole body, and sets on fire the course
        of nature; and it is set on fire by hell. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For every kind of beast and bird, of reptile and creature of the
        sea, is tamed and has been tamed by mankind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But no man can tame the tongue. It  is an unruly evil, full of deadly
        poison. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'With it we bless our God and Father, and with it we curse men, who
        have been made in the similitude of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Out of the same mouth proceed blessing and cursing. My brethren,
        these things ought not to be so. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Does a spring send forth fresh water and bitter from the same opening? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Heavenly Versus Demonic Wisdom'
      title: Heavenly Versus Demonic Wisdom
      number: 12
      content: Can a fig tree, my brethren, bear olives, or a grapevine bear figs?
        Thus no spring yields both salt water and fresh.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Who is wise and understanding among you? Let him show by good conduct
        that his works are  done in the meekness of wisdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But if you have bitter envy and self-seeking in your hearts, do not
        boast and lie against the truth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'This wisdom does not descend from above, but is earthly, sensual,
        demonic. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For where envy and self-seeking exist, confusion and every evil thing
        are there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But the wisdom that is from above is first pure, then peaceable,
        gentle, willing to yield, full of mercy and good fruits, without partiality
        and without hypocrisy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Now the fruit of righteousness is sown in peace by those who make
        peace.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Pride Promotes Strife'
      title: Pride Promotes Strife
      number: 1
      content: 'Where do wars and fights come from among you? Do they not come from
        your desires  for pleasure that war in your members? '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You lust and do not have. You murder and covet and cannot obtain.
        You fight and war. Yet you do not have because you do not ask. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You ask and do not receive, because you ask amiss, that you may spend
        it on your pleasures. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Adulterers and adulteresses! Do you not know that friendship with
        the world is enmity with God? Whoever therefore wants to be a friend of the
        world makes himself an enemy of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Or do you think that the Scripture says in vain, \u201CThe Spirit
        who dwells in us yearns jealously\u201D?"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Humility Cures Worldliness'
      title: Humility Cures Worldliness
      number: 6
      content: "But He gives more grace. Therefore He says:\u201CGod resists the
        proud,But gives grace to the humble.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Therefore submit to God. Resist the devil and he will flee from you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Draw near to God and He will draw near to you. Cleanse your hands,
        you sinners; and purify your hearts, you double-minded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Lament and mourn and weep! Let your laughter be turned to mourning
        and your joy to gloom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Do Not Judge a Brother'
      title: Do Not Judge a Brother
      number: 10
      content: Humble yourselves in the sight of the Lord, and He will lift you up.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Do not speak evil of one another, brethren. He who speaks evil of
        a brother and judges his brother, speaks evil of the law and judges the law.
        But if you judge the law, you are not a doer of the law but a judge. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Do Not Boast About Tomorrow'
      title: Do Not Boast About Tomorrow
      number: 12
      content: There is one Lawgiver, who is able to save and to destroy. Who are
        you to judge another?
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Come now, you who say, \u201CToday or tomorrow we will go to such
        and such a city, spend a year there, buy and sell, and make a profit\u201D; "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'whereas you do not know what will  happen tomorrow. For what is your
        life? It is even a vapor that appears for a little time and then vanishes
        away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Instead you ought to say, \u201CIf the Lord wills, we shall live
        and do this or that.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: But now you boast in your arrogance. All such boasting is evil.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Therefore, to him who knows to do good and does not do it, to him
        it is sin.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Rich Oppressors Will Be Judged'
      title: Rich Oppressors Will Be Judged
      number: 1
      content: 'Come now, you  rich, weep and howl for your miseries that are coming
        upon you!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Your riches are corrupted, and your garments are moth-eaten. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Your gold and silver are corroded, and their corrosion will be a
        witness against you and will eat your flesh like fire. You have heaped up
        treasure in the last days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Indeed the wages of the laborers who mowed your fields, which you
        kept back by fraud, cry out; and the cries of the reapers have reached the
        ears of the Lord of Sabaoth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You have lived on the earth in pleasure and luxury; you have fattened
        your hearts as in a day of slaughter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Be Patient and Persevering'
      title: Be Patient and Persevering
      number: 6
      content: You have condemned, you have murdered the just; he does not resist
        you.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Therefore be patient, brethren, until the coming of the Lord. See
        how the farmer waits for the precious fruit of the earth, waiting patiently
        for it until it receives the early and latter rain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: You also be patient. Establish your hearts, for the coming of the
        Lord is at hand.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Do not grumble against one another, brethren, lest you be condemned.
        Behold, the Judge is standing at the door! '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'My brethren, take the prophets, who spoke in the name of the Lord,
        as an example of suffering and patience. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Indeed we count them blessed who endure. You have heard of the perseverance
        of Job and seen the end intended  by the Lord\u2014that the Lord is very
        compassionate and merciful."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Meeting Specific Needs'
      title: Meeting Specific Needs
      number: 12
      content: "But above all, my brethren, do not swear, either by heaven or by
        earth or with any other oath. But let your \u201CYes\u201D be \u201CYes,\u201D
        and your \u201CNo,\u201D \u201CNo,\u201D lest you fall into judgment."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Is anyone among you suffering? Let him pray. Is anyone cheerful?
        Let him sing psalms. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Is anyone among you sick? Let him call for the elders of the church,
        and let them pray over him, anointing him with oil in the name of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the prayer of faith will save the sick, and the Lord will raise
        him up. And if he has committed sins, he will be forgiven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Confess your trespasses to one another, and pray for one another,
        that you may be healed. The effective, fervent prayer of a righteous man
        avails much. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Elijah was a man with a nature like ours, and he prayed earnestly
        that it would not rain; and it did not rain on the land for three years and
        six months. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Bring Back the Erring One'
      title: Bring Back the Erring One
      number: 18
      content: And he prayed again, and the heaven gave rain, and the earth produced
        its fruit.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Brethren, if anyone among you wanders from the truth, and someone
        turns him back, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: let him know that he who turns a sinner from the error of his way
        will save a soul from death and cover a multitude of sins.
      comments: []
